

JavaScript (script.js)
// Get all read more buttons
const readMoreButtons = document.querySelectorAll('.read-more');

// Add event listener to each button
readMoreButtons.forEach(button => {
    button.addEventListener('click', () => {
        // Get the parent element of the button (the wonder div)
        const wonderDiv = button.parentNode;
        
        // Get the more-info div within the wonder div
        const moreInfoDiv = wonderDiv.querySelector('.more-info');
        
        // Toggle the visibility of the more-info div
        moreInfoDiv.classList.toggle('visible');
        
        // Change the button text
        if (moreInfoDiv.classList.contains('visible')) {
            button.textContent = 'Read Less';
        } else {
            button.textContent = 'Read More';
        }
    });
});
CSS (add to style.css)
.more-info {
    display: none;
}

.more-info.visible {
    display: block;
}

This code uses the following techniques:

1. *QuerySelectorAll*: Selects all elements with the class `read-more` and stores them in a NodeList.
2. *AddEventListener*: Adds a click event listener to each button.
3. *ParentNode*: Gets the parent element of the button (the wonder div).
4. *QuerySelector*: Gets the `.more-info` div within the wonder div.
5. *ClassList*: Toggles the `visible` class on the `.more-info` div.
6. *TextContent*: Changes the text content of the button.

When a "Read More" button is clicked, the corresponding `.more-info` div is toggled visible, and the button text changes to "Read Less". When the button is clicked again, the `.more-info` div is hidden, and the button text changes back to "Read More".
